President Biden convened a call with allies and partners to discuss support for Ukraine as it defends against Russia's invasion. The leaders discussed providing ammunition and weapons systems to Ukraine, strengthening its air defenses, and repairing its energy infrastructure. They also talked about aligning donor efforts to support Ukraine's economic recovery and addressing energy, economic, and food security challenges caused by Russia's war. Participants on the call included Prime Minister Trudeau of Canada, President von der Leyen of the European Commission, Chancellor Scholz of Germany, and others.